The paper discusses the application of iterative belief propagation algorithms in belief networks, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of arc-consistency algorithms, which are commonly used in constraint satisfaction problems (cs.DS). The paper's focus on the convergence and soundness of belief propagation algorithms suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and possibly social networks (cs.SI) where belief propagation is also used.
